rect.title: The sum of currents entering any junction in an electric circuit is always equal to the sum of currents leaving that junction
In any closed loop in an electric circuit, the total potential rise equals to the total potential drop along that loop.
A thermistor is a resistor whose resistance decreases with increasing temperature. An LDR is a resistor whose resistance decreases with increasing light intensity.
